translated: Eklund, Oscar Filip Natanael, editorial secretary, Lönköping, born December 5th, 1897 in Huskvarna to Alfred E. and Matilda Colliin. Married to Gulli Larsson in 1927. Children: Ann-Marie, born in 1928 and a student, Bo, born in 1934 and a student. Graduated from Gothenburg's Handicraft Institute in 1920. Worked for Husqvarna Weapon Factory from 1911-1919, then became a collaborator for Jönköping-Post from 1921 and an editorial secretary from 1936. Cashier for the Småland district of the Swedish Journalist Association from 1935 and member of the board for KFUM's song association from 1944. Founder of KFUM's men's choir in Jönköping and member of the tax commission from 1943. Former secretary for Huskvarna KFUM. Hobby: singing, music.
